issue.title: Add delayed injection loading
issue.body:
This commit causes the data to load on the first sign of the page
changing, but waits until the page is loaded enough before injecting.
This means injection is fast, data loading is undetectable, and our
comments will display in synch with youtube comments. Code is pretty
hack jobby, so a basic rundown is. Load data and ready injection are
called to mark when injection is possible and when data has been loaded.
They then both call a handler which will only run the main script if
both the data is loaded and the page is ready for injection. There are
some places where the variables used to track this are reset to false.
They may appear abitrary but they have a purpose i promise ;)

issue.title: Fixed navigation detection
issue.body:
This comment now detect any youtube navigation no matter what! It works
via two paths:
a) The document is loaded for the first time (page refresh, first time
entering the link, etc). In this case it loads through the normal
process using document ready.
b) The user navigates youtube and youtube uses it's pushstate
navigation. In this case there is a listener on the waiting for a div by
the name of watch7-container. This is the main container for comments
and other non video related content. This was the best option that loads
the fastest while still assuring #watch-discussion is loaded for the
injection script. This means if the #watch7-container id is deprecated,
the extension will cease to work and if our extension fails somewhere
doesn the line, this is the first place to look!
